<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                            <head>[Telegram.—Translation.]</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-06"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                        1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                            <p>The board of provisional government of the Republic of Panama has
                                appointed Señor Philippe Bunau Varilla envoy extraordinary and
                                minister plenipotentiary near your Government with full powers to
                                conduct diplomatic and financial negotiations. Deign to receive and
                                heed him.</p>
                            <closer><signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">J. M. Arango</hi>,</item>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Tomas Arias</hi>,</item>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Federico Boyd</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations.</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>